edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.Models

Class AstronautModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.Obstacles.Obstacle
      • edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.Obstacles.SimpleObstacle
        • edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.Obstacles.CapsuleObstacle
          • edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.Models.AstronautModel

  • public class AstronautModel
extends CapsuleObstacle
    Avatar avatar for the plaform game. Note that this class returns to static loading. That is because there are no other subclasses that we might loop through.

      • AstronautModel

        public AstronautModel(float width,
                      float height,
                      boolean active,
                      boolean playerOne)
        Creates a new dude at the origin. The size is expressed in physics units NOT pixels. In order for drawing to work properly, you MUST set the drawScale. The drawScale converts the physics units to pixels.
        Parameters:
        width - The object width in physics units
        height - The object width in physics units

      • AstronautModel

      • AstronautModel

        public AstronautModel(float x,
                      float y,
                      float width,
                      float height,
                      boolean active,
                      boolean playerOne)
        Creates a new dude avatar at the given position. The size is expressed in physics units NOT pixels. In order for drawing to work properly, you MUST set the drawScale. The drawScale drawing to work properly, you MUST set the drawScale. The drawScaled converts the physics units to pixels.
        Parameters:
        x - Initial x position of the avatar center
        y - Initial y position of the avatar center
        width - The object width in physics units
        height - The object width in physics units
